From 1c8e934e67aba65dfd03ce59f7159fe0f59cec9e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohammed Naser <mnaser@vexxhost.com>
Date: Thu, 19 Feb 2026 11:47:36 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Fix OVN network log cross-project drop event attribution

When network log resources are created for specific security groups,
drop events were incorrectly attributed across projects because all
ports share a single global neutron_pg_drop port group. When the log
driver enabled logging on neutron_pg_drop's ACLs, drops from all VMs
across all projects were stamped with a single log resource name.

This change introduces per-security-group drop ACLs for correct log
attribution:

- Lower neutron_pg_drop priority from 1001 to 1000
- Add ACL_PRIORITY_LOG_DROP = 1001 for per-SG logged drops
- When a log resource targets a specific SG with DROP/ALL events,
  create drop ACLs at priority 1001 on that SG's port group with
  log=true and the correct log resource name
- Ports without logging fall through to the silent global drop at 1000
- Add maintenance task to migrate existing neutron_pg_drop ACLs from
  priority 1001 to 1000

Priority ordering: 1002 (ALLOW per-SG) > 1001 (DROP+LOG per-SG) >
1000 (DROP neutron_pg_drop silent safety net)

Closes-Bug: #2110087

Generated-by: GitHub Copilot (Claude Opus 4.6)
Change-Id: I61a9c7e5bf85a8d5d9c4aa58da83e46a7d5fc108
Signed-off-by: Mohammed Naser <mnaser@vexxhost.com>
